{"article_id":"hcCxHWlLdosMTMK9","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Two pivotal Senate Republicans","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"- Susan Collins of Maine and Mitt Romney of Utah -","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"announced Thursday","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"they would vote to subpoena witnesses in the impeachment trial of President Donald Trump ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"but it remained unclear whether there were enough votes for additional testimony .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"Both were expected to join Democrats in voting to subpoena witnesses such as former national security adviser John Bolton , along with potential swing votes from GOP Sens . Lamar Alexander of Tennessee and Lisa Murkowski of Alaska","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"\" I worked with other senators","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"to make sure","depth":12},{"id":9,"text":"that we have the right","depth":13},{"id":10,"text":"to ask for more documents and witnesses ,","depth":13},{"id":11,"text":"but there is no need for more evidence","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"to prove something","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"that has already been proven","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"and that does not meet the United States Constitution ' s high bar for an impeachable offense , ''","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"Alexander said .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"'The Russians are coming ' :","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Moments from a busy day in Congress and the impeachment trial","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"The announcements turned all eyes on Murkowski ,","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"who told reporters","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"she is still weighing her options .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"\" I am going to go reflect on what I have heard ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"re-read my notes","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"and decide","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"whether I need to hear more , ''","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"Because a majority of the Senate sets policy in the trial ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"the 47 Senate Democrats need at least four of the 53 Republicans","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"to support subpoenas","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"to summon witnesses or documents ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"as House managers have urged .","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"The Senate is expected to vote Friday on subpoenas .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"A motion","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"to subpoena a witness","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"would fail on a 50-50 tie .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"It 's not clear whether Supreme Court Chief Justice John Roberts ,","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"who is presiding ,","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"would break the tie .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Alexander , Collins , Murkowski and Romney were among a handful of Republican senators","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"who kept open the possibility","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"of calling witnesses as House Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"who prosecuted the case ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"and Trump 's defense team each presented three days of opening arguments .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"Senators posed written questions for both sides during eight-sessions Wednesday and Thursday .","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"Bolton 's offer became more urgent","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"after the New York Times reported","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"that his pending book described Trump telling his aide","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"that he suspended $ 391 million in military assistance to Ukraine under the condition of investigations of former Vice President Joe Biden and his son , Hunter .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"But Trump has denied telling Bolton","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"that the Ukraine aid was tied to investigations .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"He also suggested","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"he might fight to block Bolton 's testimony under executive privilege ,","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"to protect the confidentiality of advice from top aides .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Collins said","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"she would support witnesses","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"and said","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"if they are approved ,","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"House managers and Trump 's defense team should agree on a limited number for each side .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"The Senate could then vote on the precise number ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"`` I believe","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"hearing from certain witnesses would give each side the opportunity","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"to more fully and fairly make their case ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"resolve any ambiguities ,","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"and provide additional clarity , ''","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"Collins said .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"`` Therefore , I will vote in support of the motion","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"to allow witnesses and documents to be subpoenaed . ''","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"More :","depth":5},{"id":70,"text":"# ArrestRandPaul trends on Twitter","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"after he walks out over impeachment question","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"Murkowski offered a hint about her thinking","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"when she asked Trump 's defense team Thursday","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"why the Senate should n't call Bolton .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"`` This dispute about material facts weighs in favor","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"of calling additional witnesses with direct knowledge , ''","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"Murkowski said in the written question ,","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"read by Supreme Court Chief Justice John Roberts .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"Patrick Philbin , a deputy White House counsel , warned","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"that agreeing to call additional witnesses would establish new standards for impeachment ,","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"if the House can send `` half-baked '' cases","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"and leave the Senate to complete the investigation .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"Philbin also said","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"Bolton had n't confirmed the newspaper report .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"\" It will do grave damage to this body as an institution to say","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"that the proceedings in the House don ' t have to really be complete , ''","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"Philbin said .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"\" That ' s not the way the way","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"that his chamber should allow impeachments to be presented to it . ''","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"The clash over witnesses has been contentious throughout the trial .","depth":4},{"id":91,"text":"As the trial opened ,","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"the Senate rejected Democratic proposals for witnesses in a series of party-line votes ,","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"but held out the prospect for more votes","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"after arguments and questions were done .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"House managers","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"led by Intelligence Chairman Adam Schiff , D-Calif. ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"the trial would n't be fair","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"without compelling witnesses","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"who refused to testify during the impeachment inquiry , including Bolton and acting White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"Schiff argued","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"that the House could n't wait for courts to enforce subpoenas","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"because an appeals decision is still pending for former White House counsel Don McGahn ,","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"while Trump represents a threat to the 2020 election .","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"\" He will not be acquitted , \"","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"House Speaker Nancy Pelosi , D-Calif. , told reporters Thursday about Trump .","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"\" You can not be acquitted","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"if you don ' t have a trial .","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"And you don ' t have a trial","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"if you don ' t have witnesses and documentation . \"","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"But Trump ' s defense team said","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"the House should have summoned witnesses","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"and fought in court","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"to enforce subpoenas .","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"Jay Sekulow , another defense lawyer , argued","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"that no witnesses were needed","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"because the House managers said","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"they already had overwhelming evidence","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"to prove their case .","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"But Sekulow said","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"Trump 's team would want to call its own witnesses","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"if any were allowed .","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"Sekulow said","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"he would like to call Joe Biden , Hunter Biden and the whistleblower ,","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"whose complaint about Trump 's dealings with Ukraine sparked the impeachment inquiry .","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"Trump 's lawyers said","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"the trial could last months longer","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"if senators open the door to witnesses .","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"But Schiff suggested","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"that witnesses could be deposed within a week","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"and that Supreme Court Chief Justice John Roberts ,","depth":15},{"id":132,"text":"who is presiding over the trial ,","depth":15},{"id":133,"text":"could quickly resolve disputes","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"over which witnesses are relevant","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"and which deserve executive privilege .","depth":14}],"relations":[{"parent":271,"left":0,"right":